# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore — what does NOT enter the build context.
#
# Why this matters:
#   * Anything in the build context is sent to the Docker daemon on every
#     build. Large folders (venv/, data/) make builds slow and waste disk.
#   * Anything in the build context *can* end up in the image if a COPY
#     ever widens. Keeping secrets and data OUT is defence in depth.
#   * `.env` in an image is how API keys leak to public registries. Rule:
#     never COPY .env. Inject secrets at runtime via --env-file or
#     docker-compose env_file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Python virtualenv & bytecode ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# We rebuild deps inside the image. The host venv has wrong arch/glibc anyway.
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env must NEVER be baked into the image. It's mounted or env-file'd at run.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Runtime state ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are BIND-MOUNTED at runtime so the container writes to the host.
# Copying them into the image would baffle debugging ("why is old data here?")
# and balloon the image size.
data/
logs/

# ── Legacy / scripts not needed at runtime ──────────────────────────────────
# Collector.py is kept in the repo for narrative; the container only needs
# Collectorv2.py. The scripts/ folder holds one-off utilities (API_test.py,
# get_channel_id.py) that don't belong in the runtime image.
ingestion/Collector.py
ingestion/__init__.py
scripts/
video_stats.csv

# ── Docs / dev files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
docs/
*.md
!README.md
Makefile

# ── Git / editor metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Docker itself ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Don't COPY these into the image — recursive weirdness.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
